The right approach in the tests is Playwright's `toPass()` retry pattern — click the button, assert the outcome, and let Playwright retry the whole block if it fails:

```ts
await expect(async () => {
    await submitButton.click();
    await expect(page.getByText('Name is required')).toBeVisible({ timeout: 1000 });
}).toPass();
```

This means "keep clicking submit until the validation error appears", which naturally handles the hydration window without touching the component. Want me to update the tests to use this pattern?

